Against this backdrop, the administration released thousands of pages of JFK assassination files, touting \'93maximum transparency.\'94 The release mattered for historians and for the public record. But in the balance of the week, it was outweighed by the contemporaneous erasure and manipulation of current information: the silencing of international broadcasters, the narrowing of access to student loan tools, the removal of disability and gun\uc0\u8209 violence advisories, and the recasting of military history to downplay the contributions of minorities. Memory, in this environment, was curated by those in power. What could not be controlled was at risk of being erased.\
