Yet even in this darkening landscape, pockets of institutional resilience remained. Federal judges blocked the administration\'92s attempt to claw back $20 billion in climate grants from the EPA, preserving funding for environmental initiatives. Another judge halted a new ban on transgender individuals serving in the military, calling it \'93unabashedly demeaning\'94 and \'93soaked in animus.\'94 Courts limited the scope of executive orders aimed at terminating DEI programs, even as an appeals court lifted an earlier, broader block. State attorneys general secured temporary restraining orders against firings and funding freezes, and when the administration tried to \'93pause\'94 grants, they returned to court to enforce compliance. In Alabama, a Republican governor signed a bill banning devices that convert pistols into machine guns, a reminder that not all uses of state power in this period ran in the same direction.\
